resumeSummary:
Rahul Sharma is an enthusiastic, seasoned Java Developer with solid experience spanning five years (2021 – present). He holds a B.Tech degree in Computer Science from XYZ Institute of Technology located in Mumbai, India. Rahul's skill set includes proficient knowledge and application of MySQL for database management alongside his expertise using Git and GitHub as version control systems. Additionally, he possesses basic skills in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to complement web development tasks.

During his tenure at a Mumbai-based tech firm from 2018 - 2025, Rahul contributed significantly with over two years of experience as an Application Developer focusing on backend systems using Java. He demonstrated strong technical skills in database management and web development technologies such as HTML/CSS for UI design while also utilizing PHP to develop server-side functionalities.

Rahul has honed his SQL programming abilities by creating complex queries, reporting mechanisms, data warehousing strategies using Oracle Database during a six months' stint at ABC Corporation in Bangalore from 2016 - 2018 as an Intern and Software Developer.

With five years of experience under his belt since joining Mumbai-based tech firm DEF Technology, Rahul has successfully built multiple software solutions for internal teams using Java with JDBC technology while also having hands-on exposure to MySQL server administration during a six months' stint at GHI Solutions in Delhi as an Intern (2015 - 2016).

Rahul is adept and has successfully completed projects across various domains such as Library Management System, using his skills with JDBC/MySQL; Online Storefront for a Retail Company focusing on backend operations while also developing front-end components in HTML/CSS alongside REST API services developed through PHP. His proficiency extends to handling data integration tasks by implementing complex SQL queries and reporting mechanisms utilizing Oracle Database during his internship experience at ABC Corporation (2016 - 2018).

In conclusion, Rahul is a strong candidate for any Java developer role with an impressive skill set in web development technologies such as HTML/CSS and JavaScript. His expertise extends to database management systems like MySQL and Oracle Database coupled with excellent knowledge of version control platforms including Git and GitHub; which makes him not only highly sought after but also versatile enough to handle multiple domains within the IT industry ranging from library system, retail storefronts to data integration tasks during his tenure in various organizations. His passion for learning has enabled Rahul continuously grow technically as well as professionally throughout these years working with several esteemed companies and tackling a diverse set of challenging projects along the way - qualities that make him an exceptional asset any tech firm would be proud to have on board their team.
